you used to know.

66
00:08:59,630 --> 00:09:01,620
Alright.
See you soon.

67
00:09:02,266 --> 00:09:04,626
Yeah, see you soon...

68
00:09:04,768 --> 00:09:07,528
But it's better for me
to stay here.

69
00:09:07,972 --> 00:09:08,732
Hey!

70
00:09:09,673 --> 00:09:11,833
You never listen!

71
00:09:25,289 --> 00:09:26,549
What is that?

72
00:09:29,093 --> 00:09:32,463
I don't know.
What should we do?

73
00:09:32,596 --> 00:09:37,466
What's the problem?
Just take it with you.

74
00:10:01,926 --> 00:10:06,796
Oh, my god.
I see a disaster and illness.

75
00:10:07,331 --> 00:10:11,891
You can't change your fate,
but you can change the future.

76
00:10:12,436 --> 00:10:17,196
You need a strong will
and preparation, right?

77
00:10:17,441 --> 00:10:19,411
What kind of preparation?

78
00:10:19,543 --> 00:10:24,913
Is it okay if I give you
some advice?

79
00:10:25,049 --> 00:10:26,809
Of course it is.

80
00:10:32,856 --> 00:10:37,416
It's not like any other insurance.
You only need to pay...

81
00:10:37,661 --> 00:10:39,721
What are you doing?

82
00:10:43,367 --> 00:10:45,027
How much do we have
to pay for nursery school?

83
00:10:45,169 --> 00:10:47,329
How about home schooling
her myself?

84
00:10:47,471 --> 00:10:50,031
Then she would have
even less friend than now.

85
00:10:50,774 --> 00:10:53,944
I'll pay the bills, later.

86
00:10:54,078 --> 00:10:55,338
Debt Repayment Reminder

87
00:10:55,779 --> 00:10:57,839
You think about medical bills.

88
00:11:00,918 --> 00:11:03,078
A suitcase?
Don't open it.

89
00:11:03,220 --> 00:11:05,190
Why not?
I have to find the owner.

90
00:11:05,623 --> 00:11:09,083
Your fate changes
once you open that bag.

91
00:11:09,226 --> 00:11:12,886
It is? Then I really
have to open it.

92
00:11:17,034 --> 00:11:19,004
I told you not to touch it.

93
00:11:20,838 --> 00:11:23,898
I didn't open it.
It opened itself.

94
00:11:24,041 --> 00:11:24,911
Eun-Seo?

95
00:11:25,142 --> 00:11:27,012
She's not sleeping?
Let me talk to her.

96
00:11:31,248 --> 00:11:33,908
No, she's sleeping.

97
00:12:13,023 --> 00:12:14,393
Hello?

98
00:12:15,426 --> 00:12:16,886
Did you steal my bag?

99
00:12:17,127 --> 00:12:19,987
Not me.

100
00:12:22,332 --> 00:12:24,102
Someone wants to talk to you.

101
00:12:28,138 --> 00:12:30,198
The king lived here, right?

102
00:12:30,941 --> 00:12:33,811
- Where are you?
- I'm going up.

103
00:12:34,344 --> 00:12:37,714
You have to come up
some more.

104
00:12:37,848 --> 00:12:38,818
More?

105
00:12:38,949 --> 00:12:40,609
I think you'll be here.

106
00:12:41,452 --> 00:12:43,112
Can't you see me?

107
00:12:44,455 --> 00:12:47,615
No, nothing.

108
00:12:48,358 --> 00:12:49,918
Put your hands up.

109
00:13:04,308 --> 00:13:05,368
What the...

110
00:13:15,819 --> 00:13:17,679
The bag!

111
00:13:35,038 --> 00:13:36,398
Get the bag.

112
00:13:37,941 --> 00:13:39,201
Me?

113
00:13:41,745 --> 00:13:43,005
I can't.

114
00:13:55,159 --> 00:13:56,919
Help me!

115
00:14:19,616 --> 00:14:21,476
Hey, you got old.

116
00:14:21,718 --> 00:14:24,588
I have two kids.
It's not surprising.

117
00:14:24,721 --> 00:14:26,591
Oh, yes.
You got married again.

118
00:14:27,024 --> 00:14:30,984
Yes, I did.
And they died.

119
00:14:31,128 --> 00:14:32,388
Why?

120
00:14:32,729 --> 00:14:35,889
Stop following me!

121
00:14:37,935 --> 00:14:39,595
Where's the emergency?

122
00:14:44,041 --> 00:14:45,301
There he is.

123
00:14:46,543 --> 00:14:48,413
He's fine.

124
00:14:48,946 --> 00:14:52,396
I told you to be careful!
I had a bad dream.

125
00:15:01,291 --> 00:15:03,261
We're here.

126
00:15:30,621 --> 00:15:32,181
My friend needs money.

127
00:15:32,823 --> 00:15:36,693
So I bought it at a fair price
for quick sale.

128
00:15:37,427 --> 00:15:41,187
You can sleep and work
in here.

129
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:44,202
You can do literally
everything in here.

130
00:15:44,835 --> 00:15:47,895
You see, some years ago...

131
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:52,110
This was a room
for many champions.

132
00:15:54,444 --> 00:16:00,114
Hey, I understand.
This is one lousy office.

133
00:16:00,350 --> 00:16:05,250
But the rent fee is so cheap.
You don't have money, right?

134
00:16:15,198 --> 00:16:16,668
I like it.

135
00:16:20,003 --> 00:16:26,883
Our next guest is JEONG lm-bok,
adopted to Canada in 1986.

136
00:16:27,010 --> 00:16:28,810
