The Music Festival!

573
01:00:39,660 --> 01:00:42,930
It's a sweet melody.

574
01:00:43,064 --> 01:00:44,624
Feel your dream.

575
01:00:49,070 --> 01:00:53,440
Those boys are too skinny.
Just like a skeleton.

576
01:00:57,979 --> 01:01:00,039
Can't understand them.

577
01:01:02,516 --> 01:01:04,476
I can't understand you.

578
01:02:12,820 --> 01:02:15,080
You haven't changed.

579
01:02:15,923 --> 01:02:17,583
I missed you.

580
01:02:19,126 --> 01:02:20,386
Always.

581
01:02:23,330 --> 01:02:28,290
I missed you, too.

582
01:02:30,738 --> 01:02:32,398
Mommy.

583
01:02:36,444 --> 01:02:38,614
Mommy, remember me?
It's Imbok.

584
01:02:38,746 --> 01:02:42,196
I became a star for you.
I want to meet you.

585
01:02:44,051 --> 01:02:48,011
Where are you? I miss you.
Come to me. I'm right here.

586
01:02:48,155 --> 01:02:51,215
Don't be sorry.
I'm here, look at me.

587
01:02:51,559 --> 01:02:53,319
You're my life.

588
01:02:53,461 --> 01:02:57,121
I miss you. I love you.
That's it.

589
01:02:58,666 --> 01:03:03,866
Is that what you call
the long-waited reunion?

590
01:03:07,108 --> 01:03:12,168
I think they love
each other too much.

591
01:03:15,416 --> 01:03:17,076
I'm sorry.

592
01:03:21,622 --> 01:03:23,892
I'm really sorry.

593
01:03:44,645 --> 01:03:45,605
What're you doing?

594
01:03:48,048 --> 01:03:49,108
Where's the others?

595
01:03:53,154 --> 01:03:55,714
You should've called me,
or go to a hospital.

596
01:03:56,157 --> 01:03:59,517
Just sitting here
like a child!

597
01:04:00,261 --> 01:04:01,461
I'm fine.

598
01:04:20,514 --> 01:04:21,674
Let me see.

599
01:04:23,717 --> 01:04:25,477
Didn't you know
it would explode?

600
01:04:27,621 --> 01:04:28,591
No.

601
01:04:28,823 --> 01:04:31,383
They are things you shouldn't
put in a microwave.

602
01:04:32,526 --> 01:04:33,686
Shut up.

603
01:04:38,132 --> 01:04:39,392
When I first met you,

604
01:04:40,034 --> 01:04:45,704
you said you don't want to
perform or talk on TV show.

605
01:04:48,142 --> 01:04:52,102
But you look happy now.

606
01:04:52,246 --> 01:04:56,106
Hey, don't move.

607
01:04:57,251 --> 01:04:58,811
You'll get hurt.

608
01:05:01,188 --> 01:05:07,748
You feel affection towards
something you touch or see.

609
01:05:10,297 --> 01:05:11,757
Don't move.

610
01:05:16,203 --> 01:05:17,763
Are they a couple?

611
01:05:29,216 --> 01:05:30,266
Do you have time?

612
01:05:32,019 --> 01:05:33,079
Me?

613
01:05:43,931 --> 01:05:48,701
Do you like me?

614
01:05:50,237 --> 01:05:51,697
Yes, I do.

615
01:05:54,842 --> 01:05:59,112
You shouldn't.
We can't be a couple.

616
01:06:00,347 --> 01:06:03,247
I like you as a fan.

617
01:06:11,992 --> 01:06:13,762
Well, in that case...

618
01:06:15,796 --> 01:06:17,756
One, two, three.

619
01:06:21,302 --> 01:06:22,772
Nice picture.

620
01:06:23,203 --> 01:06:26,873
My niece is your huge fan.

621
01:06:27,508 --> 01:06:28,768
Thank you.

622
01:06:29,009 --> 01:06:32,469
No, thank you for
taking a picture with me.

623
01:06:34,615 --> 01:06:38,065
Eugene, do you know?

624
01:06:41,021 --> 01:06:43,491
You remind me of Ji-hoon.

625
01:06:45,526 --> 01:06:47,386
I do?

626
01:07:18,792 --> 01:07:19,852
Mr. Children

627
01:07:26,600 --> 01:07:28,070
That's what I love to do.

628
01:07:28,202 --> 01:07:30,072
You can't stop,
because I'm the truth.

629
01:07:30,204 --> 01:07:31,574
I just want to dance.

630
01:07:32,406 --> 01:07:35,066
I have a bad cold.

631
01:07:36,610 --> 01:07:37,770
But I'll try my best.

632
01:07:39,613 --> 01:07:41,273
Summer...

633
01:07:42,716 --> 01:07:45,776
But you have me.

634
01:07:45,919 --> 01:07:51,979
We'll dream forever.

635
01:07:58,332 --> 01:08:03,532
Poor, rough and raw.

636
01:08:05,172 --> 01:08:09,942
- What?
- But I can hear it.

637
01:08:11,779 --> 01:08:13,839
I will make you a singer.

638
01:08:14,481 --> 01:08:18,541
So everyone can hear it.

639
01:08:38,005 --> 01:08:40,765
Where have you been?

640
01:08:51,618 --> 01:08:53,678
- Get out.
- Why?

641
01:08:56,323 --> 01:08:58,093
You didn't want me
to see this?

642
01:08:58,725 --> 01:09:00,485
- It's none of your business.
- It is.

643
01:09:00,627 --> 01:09:03,317
I think it has a lot
to do with me.

644
01:09:07,968 --> 01:09:11,228
- What do you feel about him?
- What?

645
01:09:12,172 --> 01:09:14,542
Am I a substitute
for KIM Ji-hoon?

646
01:09:15,976 --> 01:09:18,136
So you can feel better?

647
01:09:20,080 --> 01:09:23,240
- Cuz I'm living out his dream?
- Shut up.

648
01:09:23,383 --> 01:09:27,753
Okay, I'll be KIM Ji-hoon.
I'll sing, dance and everything.

649
01:09:28,789 --> 01:09:30,849
Then kill myself like him, right?

650
01:09:34,194 --> 01:09:41,574
I needed someone to replace him
and you were the right person.

651
01:09:43,203 --> 01:09:44,573
Do you know

652
01:09:48,208 --> 01:09:50,678
what hurts me the most?

653
01:09:55,015 --> 01:10:00,575
That I was another
Ji-hoon for you.

654
01:10:04,224 --> 01:10:08,994
Eugene didn't exist to you.

655
01:10:19,840 --> 01:10:24,500
- The winner of this week is
- Mr. Children, Congratulations!

656
01:10:24,645 --> 01:10:28,805
You won 4 weeks in a row and
earned a ticket to the Festival!

657
01:10:29,049 --> 01:10:34,109
It's time to say goodbye.
Thank you for watching.

658
01:10:39,459 --> 01:10:40,819
Simon SA

659
01:10:55,776 --> 01:10:59,226
I am nothing
without you.

660
01:10:59,580 --> 01:11:03,280
You broke my heart
but I wait for you.

661
01:11:03,417 --> 01:11:06,677
I'm tired of waiting.
I'm out of my mind.

662
01:11:06,820 --> 01:11:10,780
I just can't get over you.

663
01:11:10,924 --> 01:11:13,394
Tell me, tell me.
Oh why?

664
01:11:13,527 --> 01:11:18,587
I don't want to love
anybody.

665
01:11:18,732 --> 01:11:21,502
Tell me, tell me.
Oh why?

666
01:11:21,835 --> 01:11:25,785
Please, come back to me.

667
01:11:26,039 --> 01:11:29,699
I'm ravaged.

668
01:11:29,843 --> 01:11:32,113
Without you, I'm...

669
01:11:32,246 --> 01:11:35,306
I'm ravaged.

670
01:11:37,050 --> 01:11:43,110
This part is so difficult.
There're things you can't do.

671
01:11:46,059 --> 01:11:51,429
You turned a rocker to an Idol.
Well done, O Gu-ju.

672
01:11:52,366 --> 01:11:53,826
What do you want?

673
01:11:56,870 --> 01:11:58,240
Star Music
Artist Transfer Contract

674
01:11:58,572 --> 01:12:02,472
If you play a game with me,
you will lose.

675
01:12:02,609 --> 01:12:03,769
So?

676
01:12:03,910 --> 01:12:08,780
They're doing great.
I mean Wonder Boys.

677
01:12:09,716 --> 01:12:14,086
But they won't last long.
They are too fragile.

678
01:12:14,521 --> 01:12:19,691
They don't have tenacity.
You know what I mean?

679
01:12:20,427 --> 01:12:22,287
Actually, they can't sing.

680
01:12:22,429 --> 01:12:26,699
I was thinking about
making a visual rock band.

681
01:12:28,035 --> 01:12:31,095
Mr. Children will be perfect.

682
01:12:33,240 --> 01:12:35,900
Hand them to me
when they hit the top.

683
01:12:36,543 --> 01:12:38,913
Those boys were mine.

684
01:12:40,247 --> 01:12:43,707
It's better for you
and the members.

685
01:12:44,251 --> 01:12:47,811
Or will you run off again
after one of them dies?

686
01:12:57,764 --> 01:13:02,264
You can't even keep
a microphone with care.

687
01:13:31,231 --> 01:13:42,701
You hold my hand
and stayed by my side.

688
01:13:42,843 --> 01:13:48,413
Now, I can feel
your heart.

689
01:13:54,654 --> 01:13:56,524
Eugene!

690
01:14:03,797 --> 01:14:05,257
Idol pop groups?

691
01:14:08,201 --> 01:14:09,261
Trash.

692
01:14:10,904 --> 01:14:12,874
They are stupid.

693
01:14:13,907 --> 01:14:18,667
I think music should
feed your soul.

694
01:14:18,812 --> 01:14:22,512
Eugene of Mr. Children.
His controversial remarks on Idols!

695
01:14:26,520 --> 01:14:32,190
Mr. Children is temporarily banned
from TVshow programs,

696
01:14:32,325 --> 01:14:36,185
and it remains uncertain whether
they can be seen at the Music Festival,

697
01:14:36,329 --> 01:14:38,299
the biggest K-pop event.

698
01:14:38,432 --> 01:14:43,502
The agency 'Champion' hasn't
made any announcement yet.

699
01:14:49,843 --> 01:14:54,303
My boss blamed me for
losing ads because of this.

700
01:14:55,949 --> 01:14:58,709
This video clip thing
is quite serious.

701
01:15:01,288 --> 01:15:05,548
It's better for them to skip
this week's show.

702
01:15:05,692 --> 01:15:09,462
I'm verifying the video.
I'll take care of it.

703
01:15:11,498 --> 01:15:12,758
Give me some time.

704
01:15:13,900 --> 01:15:15,160
O Gu-ju.

705
01:15:18,505 --> 01:15:19,665
I am sorry...

706
01:15:34,721 --> 01:15:35,881
We gotta talk.

707
01:15:36,223 --> 01:15:37,193
Listen.

708
01:15:43,129 --> 01:15:44,189
What is it?

709
01:15:44,831 --> 01:15:46,491
I didn't say that.

710
01:15:46,833 --> 01:15:49,603
You didn't?
What a relief.

711
01:15:50,937 --> 01:15:52,397
Then prove it.

712
01:15:53,340 --> 01:15:54,810
I was just...

713
01:15:57,844 --> 01:16:00,614
- I mean...
- Whatever you say...

714
01:16:00,747 --> 01:16:02,647
Nothing changes.

715
01:16:03,083 --> 01:16:04,243
Go home.

716
01:16:11,992 --> 01:16:16,762
LEE Eugene was a singer
in underground band,

717
01:16:16,897 --> 01:16:19,157
when he took this video.

718
01:16:19,399 --> 01:16:20,759
Whatever the reason may be,

719
01:16:21,301 --> 01:16:25,571
his thoughtless action has
disappointed many fans.

720
01:16:25,705 --> 01:16:27,865
And he caused trouble
to related people.

721
01:16:28,308 --> 01:16:32,268
Once again, I apologize
for his behavior.

722
01:16:32,412 --> 01:16:33,782
We'll take questions.

723
01:16:35,015 --> 01:16:37,175
Is it true Eugene will
drop out of the team?

724
01:16:37,317 --> 01:16:38,477
It's not true.

725
01:16:38,618 --> 01:16:41,278
I heard you're searching
for a new member.

726
01:16:41,421 --> 01:16:42,391
Not true.

727
01:16:42,522 --> 01:16:44,292
What about the
other members?

728
01:16:44,824 --> 01:16:48,284
Jio was arrested for
assault in San Diego.

729
01:16:48,428 --> 01:16:50,988
He was booked without
detention in Korea, twice.

730
01:16:51,131 --> 01:16:53,691
Ricky is an illegal immigrant
with double nationality.

731
01:16:53,833 --> 01:16:57,103
Hyun has a girlfriend
and a baby.

732
01:16:57,237 --> 01:17:00,927
These things are their
private lives of the past.

733
01:17:01,074 --> 01:17:06,644
People say that if the rumors
are true, they should break up.

734
01:17:06,980 --> 01:17:09,350
There are so many
pop groups nowadays,

735
01:17:09,583 --> 01:17:12,643
but many are unqualified.

736
01:17:12,786 --> 01:17:14,746
It's definitely a social problem.

737
01:17:15,288 --> 01:17:17,848
Music industry is
not a rehab.

738
01:17:17,991 --> 01:17:21,861
Excuse me but that
sounds like an offense.

739
01:17:21,995 --> 01:17:22,955
You're right.

740
01:17:24,397 --> 01:17:26,057
I agree with you.

741
01:17:28,001 --> 01:17:31,661
So Mr. Children sang.

742
01:17:32,606 --> 01:17:36,566
It was the only thing
they could do.

743
01:17:37,010 --> 01:17:41,470
They sang, dance and mend
their hearts with music.

744
01:17:42,015 --> 01:17:43,675
Music was their dream.

745
01:17:43,817 --> 01:17:46,177
Is that even relevant?

746
01:17:46,620 --> 01:17:50,680
They can't make a
clean break with the past

747
01:17:50,824 --> 01:17:55,094
But what they put in music

748
01:17:55,729 --> 01:17:56,789
It was real.

749
01:17:56,930 --> 01:18:01,330
Do we have to sit out the
whole play until one dies?

750
01:18:01,468 --> 01:18:02,228
Bullshit!

751
01:18:02,369 --> 01:18:03,839
What the fuck is this!

752
01:18:05,171 --> 01:18:06,931
You blaming us for all this?

753
01:18:07,173 --> 01:18:09,643
- You know nothing!
- Stop it.

754
01:18:13,480 --> 01:18:14,340
Eugene.

755
01:18:18,785 --> 01:18:20,945
I apologize for having
caused trouble.

756
01:18:21,988 --> 01:18:26,448
This is all my fault.

757
01:18:26,793 --> 01:18:32,163
If the members can't
perform because of me!?

758
01:18:32,699 --> 01:18:33,859
From now on,

759
01:18:35,902 --> 01:18:38,062
I will drop out of Mr. Children.

760
01:18:39,806 --> 01:18:42,666
You mean you'll stop
your career as a singer?

761
01:18:42,809 --> 01:18:44,569
What about Mr. Children?

762
01:18:44,711 --> 01:18:46,371
Tell us some more!

763
01:18:48,415 --> 01:18:49,465
LEE Eugene.

764
01:18:50,016 --> 01:18:51,066
Eugene!

765
01:18:51,718 --> 01:18:53,578
Just a moment!

766
01:19:09,369 --> 01:19:14,739
Wonder Boys records sales
hit 0.3 million.

767
01:19:43,203 --> 01:19:46,473
- What is this?
- Rainbow spicy noodle.

768
01:19:55,715 --> 01:19:56,975
The noodles are tough.

769
01:19:57,717 --> 01:19:58,977
I like it.

770
01:20:06,826 --> 01:20:08,686
So what will you do?

771
01:20:09,229 --> 01:20:13,289
People will recognize you.

772
01:20:15,335 --> 01:20:17,495
You said I should
take over the restaurant.

773
01:20:21,441 --> 01:20:24,411
Are you going to cook
with that face?

774
01:20:25,044 --> 01:20:30,614
You have to feel happy
when you're cooking.

775
01:20:33,052 --> 01:20:35,022
If you cook with a smile
on your face,

776
01:20:37,457 --> 01:20:40,717
the dish will be delicious
and the customer smiles!

777
01:20:40,860 --> 01:20:44,420
Dad, smile.

778
01:20:51,371 --> 01:20:53,741
You smiled a lot
on television.

779
01:22:17,624 --> 01:22:22,494
You ran away like that
and end up being here?

780
01:22:24,530 --> 01:22:25,900
I'll ask one thing.

781
01:22:27,433 --> 01:22:31,393
You don't want to be
Mr. Children anymore?

782
01:22:32,639 --> 01:22:36,909
This place suits me better.

783
01:22:37,543 --> 01:22:39,103
That was our dream.

784
01:22:40,747 --> 01:22:41,807
It was.

785
01:22:42,448 --> 01:22:43,708
Then do it.

786
01:22:44,550 --> 01:22:46,110
It's not a dream, now.

787
01:22:48,755 --> 01:22:53,815
And dreams never
come true.

788
01:23:11,611 --> 01:23:13,171
Why are you leaving?

789
01:23:14,614 --> 01:23:16,584
It's not your fault.

790
01:23:18,918 --> 01:23:22,788
You grew into a habit
of flying abroad.

791
01:23:25,625 --> 01:23:26,985
Gu-ju.

792
01:23:28,027 --> 01:23:30,187
How about we train
another group?

793
01:23:32,332 --> 01:23:34,892
A girl group, this time.

794
01:23:35,435 --> 01:23:37,595
I manage and
you write songs.

795
01:23:41,841 --> 01:23:47,211
I don't want anyone
to be hurt, again.

796
01:23:49,849 --> 01:23:52,319
